  - RZP work (Flowable-konform POC screens) → /Users/az/Downloads/rzp-alba-flowable-konform/
  - RZP worktree (exp-cleanup) → /Users/az/Downloads/rzp-alba-prototyp-worktree-exp-cleanup/
  - DexHub Alpha (tombstoned reference, read-only) → /Users/az/Downloads/test-1911-0349_dexHub-Enterprise-Alpha-1.0-master/
  - Old azamani1 targets (tombstoned) → push URL no_push://
  - AstronOne mirror (memory-only, not a working repo) → /Volumes/AstronOne/shared-memory/dexhub/

parallel_session_warning: |
  At any given time, user may have multiple Claude Code sessions open, each
  anchored in a different worktree. NEVER assume a "Phase X" request from
  the user context applies to THIS repo — verify worktree match first.
  If the user's intent is ambiguous across worktrees, ASK (don't guess).

  Specifically: RZP sessions never write into this Beta repo; this Beta
  session never writes into RZP worktrees. Shared discovery (e.g. Parser
  Pattern B) flows through memory files (`~/.claude/projects/.../memory/`),
  not through direct cross-repo commits.

